1.6.0-alpha.fa6ec338.description: A Babel plugin to wrap package modules inside AMD define() calls.
1.6.0-alpha.fa6ec338.readme:
# babel-plugin-wrap-modules-amd

> Wrap modules inside an AMD `define()` module.

## Example

**In**

```javascript
var console = require('console');
console.info('Say something');
```

**Out**

```javascript
define(['module', 'exports', 'require', 'console'], function (module, exports, require) {
	var console = require('console');
	console.log('Say something');
});
```

## Installation

```sh
npm install --save-dev babel-plugin-wrap-modules-amd
```

## Usage

Add the following to your `.babelrc` file:

```json
{
  "plugins": ["wrap-modules-amd"]
}
```

## Technical Details

This plugin wraps the code inside the module with an AMD `define()` call. The 
module is not given any name and any dependencies detected by inspecting 
`require()` calls are appended to the `define()` dependencies array so that they
can be found when `require()` is called.

1.7.0-alpha.6d6b0c8b.name: babel-plugin-wrap-modules-amd
1.7.0-alpha.6d6b0c8b.description: A Babel plugin to wrap package modules inside AMD define() calls.
1.7.0-alpha.6d6b0c8b.readme:
# babel-plugin-wrap-modules-amd

> Wrap modules inside an AMD `define()` module.

## Example

**In**

```javascript
var console = require('console');
console.info('Say something');
```

**Out**

```javascript
define(['module', 'exports', 'require', 'console'], function (module, exports, require) {
	var console = require('console');
	console.log('Say something');
});
```

## Installation

```sh
npm install --save-dev babel-plugin-wrap-modules-amd
```

## Usage

Add the following to your `.babelrc` file:

```json
{
  "plugins": ["wrap-modules-amd"]
}
```

## Technical Details

This plugin wraps the code inside the module with an AMD `define()` call. The 
module is not given any name and any dependencies detected by inspecting 
`require()` calls are appended to the `define()` dependencies array so that they
can be found when `require()` is called.

# babel-plugin-wrap-modules-amd

> Wrap modules inside an AMD `define()` module.

## Example

**In**

```javascript
var console = require('console');
console.info('Say something');
```

**Out**

```javascript
define(['module', 'exports', 'require', 'console'], function (module, exports, require) {
	var console = require('console');
	console.log('Say something');
});
```

## Installation

```sh
npm install --save-dev babel-plugin-wrap-modules-amd
```

## Usage

Add the following to your `.babelrc` file:

```json
{
  "plugins": ["wrap-modules-amd"]
}
```

## Technical Details

This plugin wraps the code inside the module with an AMD `define()` call. The 
module is not given any name and any dependencies detected by inspecting 
`require()` calls are appended to the `define()` dependencies array so that they
can be found when `require()` is called.
